
# Project Context
You are an expert Python developer building an "AI-Powered Multi-Agent Research Assistant" for a hackathon. 
The system takes a user query, searches the web, and formats the output into a structured comparison.

# Tech Stack
- Language: Python 3.10+
- Multi-Agent Framework: `pyautogen` (Microsoft AutoGen)
- LLM Provider: Groq API (using `llama3-70b-8192`)
- Search Tool: Tavily API (`requests` library)

# Coding Guidelines
- Write clean, modular, and well-commented Python code.
- Always handle API errors gracefully (e.g., if Tavily fails, return a safe fallback message).
- Prioritize execution speed and simplicity over complex abstractions.
- Never use OpenAI directly; always configure `llm_config` to use the Groq base URL (`https://api.groq.com/openai/v1`).
- When writing UI code later, assume we are using Streamlit.
- Keep agent conversations brief to avoid infinite loops.